AK "scout" mount Model M1-B 
Picatinny/Weaver style rail.

UltiMAK M1-B-- A rock-solid platform for your premium optics. With the increasing popularity of the AK based rifles in three gun competitions, the need for a handy, light, completely reliable high speed sighting system has resulted in the UltiMAK M1-B optic mount. Its Picatinny style rail is positioned well below the iron sight axis, making this the lowest optic mount available for the AK. With a tubular sight mounted low, you will be able to use your optic without a comb riser and still use your regular hold. The system allows for co witnessing (the ability to use your iron sights right through a 1x sight as a back-up sighting system) when used with a tubular reflex sight. This heavy duty mount replaces the original steel gas tube and upper handguard, so it adds less than one ounce to the weight of the rifle, making it by far the lightest optic mount installation in the world. The forward positioning of the optic gives you faster, easier and more natural targeting while maintaining your full field of view. Multiple target or moving target engagements, with both eyes open, become second nature. 
The UltiMAK AK optic mount rarely if ever needs to be removed to clean the rifle, so you need not worry about loss of zero. Since the mount is clamped to the barrel and not jammed in between the gas block and the sight block like the original gas tube, several UltiMAK users have reported an improvement in their AKs' inherent accuracy.

title: For Sale:  HK MR762 A1
location: Los Angeles - San Fernando Valley, Los Angeles, California
postcontent:
HK MR762 A1 with less than 300 rounds fired! The MR762A1 is a direct descendent of the HK416/417 series.

Using the HK-proprietary operating system, the MR762A1 is gas operated and uses a piston and a solid operating “pusher” rod in place of the common gas tube normally employed in AR15/M16/M4-style weapons. Pioneered by Heckler & Koch in the G36, HK416, and HK417; this method virtually eliminates malfunctions common to direct impingement gas systems since hot carbon fouling and waste gases do not enter the receiver area.

The MR762A1 stays cleaner, reducing heat transfer to the bolt and bolt carrier, and drastically reducing wear and tear on other critical components.

title: For Sale:  30 Round AK-47 Mag - Used Condition Varies Good to Excellent - Eastern European Military Surplus Steel Magazines
postcontent:
20 Magazines available. 

$13 each

These are 'Used' military mags from a variety of Eastern European com-bloc nations built to Soviet spec with ridge-back design. Mostly Hungarian, but there could be some other mags in the mix like Romanian, Bulgarian, Russian, Polish, Etc, Etc.  Overall a great value and at prices I have not been able to offer for over a decade on true mil-spec steel mags, not garbage-like new commercial production AK mags often sold elsewhere. Condition Varies, they could be of these grades listed below, but mostly "Very Good to Excellent" from what I have seen.  Some mags may be grease packed and need cleaning. There may be some with bent floor plates, significant finish wear, possibly some with small dents and dings that need to be popped back out to allow follower to travel freely, but we do try to sort out any that are dented to the point that follower movement is restricted so this will be minimal and easy to fix with a little effort. These are used surplus and sold "As-Is". We do diligently inspect and sort out anything unfit for use that we can identify, so damaged mags should be a relatively uncommon issue, but it is surplus so things can slip past the check process and the goods are sold "As-Is" with no warranty.

"Used, Good" meaning quite a bit if finish wear, minor surface rust, some cosmetic blemishing from storage, but functional.

"Used, Very Good" meaning some finish wear very minor surface rust, some cosmetic blemishing from storage, but functional.

"Used Excellent" meaning finish wear on edges and in fitting parts

title: For Sale:  G Code / Travis Haley INCOG Holsters
postcontent: www.Shop.PATRIOTTAC.com  The G Code / Haley Strategic INCOG inside the waistband (IWB) concealment holster is a joint development project between Travis Haley of Haley Strategic Partners and G Code Holsters. The G Code INCOG is a minimum bulk, multi-positional, deep concealment, high quality Kydex holster. Its distinctive features enable the concealed carry of a handgun from a variety of carry positions while facilitating the acquisition of a full firing grip on the weapon prior to the draw from the concealed carry. Inherent to the G Code INCOG are adjustments in the depth of concealed carry, angle of carry, the position of carry and security of carry. Adjustments are supported via the unique modular mounting points on the INCOG holster and the use of variable mounting components. Combined they maximize function respective to the users body type, concealed carry deployment tactics and personal preferences. The G Code INCOG holster is adaptive to varying operational environments and mission requirements. The mounting clip incorporates a negative angle designed to force the holster closer to the body. This improves the concealability of the holster without increasing the bulk and supports a higher positional carry without compromise to the positional security of the holster during use. This higher position facilitates faster weapon presentations from deep cover. The mounting clips also have multiple mounting points further increasing the range of carry options and adjustments. The mounting clips open and slide down over the belt and lock in place. The clip is actuated via a finger tab, and is flexed to open allowing quick installation or removal from the belt. All INCOG holsters come with Black FUZZ coating except for the Kryptek Typhon color option. Kryptek is a laminated fabric covering. At this time, PatriotTAC is ONLY selling the INCOG's with black FUZZ coating on our website. If you'd like to special order another coating/color, or ANY G-Code product, please contact us by phone, text, or e-mail.
